text: "Interlude" is a musical piece from the album "Au Pays d'Alice..." by Ibrahim Maalouf. This creation draws inspiration from Alice in Wonderland. Ibrahim collaborated with renowned rap artist Oxmo Puccino to infuse elements of jazz, rock, pop, and hip-hop, showcasing his musical creativity at its peak. With Oxmo's lyrical prowess, this album emerged as a modern and multicultural opera. The album is packed with emotions, a mellow mood, freedom, and humor. We welcome you to the wonderland of Ibrahim's magical trumpet and Oxmo's captivating lyrics.

"Doch da war mehr" is a reflective and heartrending song by Matthias Reim, included in the "Reim Deluxe Edition" album. This track contemplates a past love through poignant lyrics, with the protagonist pondering over missed opportunities and contemplating what could have been. It combines elements of schlager music, pop, and rock with an oldies feel, making it a hit in the 1990s.

"Dunce Pageant" is a song by the band "The Superweaks", featured on their album "The World Is A Terrible Place And I Hate Myself And Want To Die". The song was composed by the band itself and released through Lame-O Records in February 2014. This song, along with the rest of the album, embodies the unique melancholic yet powerful punk rock sounds of The Superweaks.

"Tus Besos Fr√≠os Como la Lluvia" (Your Kisses Cold As Rain) is a romantic salsa song by Puerto Rican singer Eddie Santiago, featured on the album "I Remain Daring." He is renowned in the world of romantic salsa. The song has been covered in the instrumental album "Salsa Instrumental Vol 4" by the group The Salsa Stars.

"No Mothers" is an alternative rock song by Mammoth Indigo from their self-titled album. This indie rock piece, written by Cody Bowers, exhibits a strong indie pop influence. The band's music, which is constantly presenting new elements fueling music discovery, can be accessed on platforms like iTunes and Spotify. Management is handled by Caitlyn Margulis from Full Circle Artist Management. The song even has an accompanying music video and a lyric video.

"Cuida de Mim" is a popular Kizomba song performed by the artist G-Amado and features in the album "Al√©m do Amor." The music was produced by DREAMBITZ and AFOBA BEATZ, written and sung by G-Amado, and recorded in the DREAMBITZ studio. This song is highly regarded in Portugal's Kizomba music scene, earning it the tag of a 'hit Kizomba.'

"The Man You Have Become" is a heartfelt song by No Limitz from the album "I Know What I Know...and that's not everything." The lyrics, written by Sherry Crawford, Dana Blayone, and Brenda Pashko, beautifully capture the proud sentiments of a mother towards her son. The song is often used as a wedding song during the mother-son dance.

"Kitty History" is a comedic song by Trevor Moore, from his album "High In Church". The song, originally performed on Comedy Central, is a satirical exploration of a parallel universe where cunning felines commit adorable war crimes. The piece combines elements of stand-up comedy, music videos, and history in a hilarious and unique way.

"Presto" is the second movement from the "Violin Concerto in B Minor" by Sir William Walton. It's a lively piece recorded under the Warner Classics label and included in the selection "Walton Violin & Viola Concerts, Partita". The London Symphony Orchestra performed the piece with Yehudi Menuhin on violin. The version was originally released in 1970 and was remastered in 1994.

"On Your Side" is a song by the artist Port St. Willow from their album "Holiday." The song was released in 2013 by Downtown Records and produced by Nicholas Principe, who also composed the lyrics. This relaxing, atmospheric track is perfect for unwinding and has been categorized under the Chill Pill playlist on YouTube.
